	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64563317"><p>That attitude in part stems from people now starting to think they are as smart on a particular subject as the scientists. During Covid, you could not swing a kneazle without hitting 10 epidemiologists who miraculously never needed a degree before they could opine to the rest of us that it was nothing more than a flu.</p><p>And the climate deniers are rarely scientists, very very rarely. Amazingly, they are able to divine it is all some hoax because the scientists are getting rich off research grants, the sun has been getting hotter, the climate was much warmer before there were humans, etc. Any excuse will do to for them to show to the rest of us their "common sense". And they repeat these tropes to each other thus building a community that believes in bullshit and are happily reinforced in their beliefs when their community parrots the same beliefs back at them: mutual co-recursive backscratching.</p></div>
	</div>

